    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - OUTPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="6">
        <title>OUTPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>When using the soft bar and maul on the output shaft, be careful not to damage the threads.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>When removing the rear bearing cover, the rear bearing cone drops from the housing bore.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the output shaft forward and through the rear bearing
                assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007b5">Figure 115</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007b5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007b5" filename="../figg13/G13007b5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 115. Drive Output Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear bearing retaining bolts from the auxiliary housing rear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007b6">Figure 116</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007b6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007b6" filename="../figg13/G13007b6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 116. Remove Rear Bearing Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear bearing cover, rear bearing and bearing race from the auxiliary housing rear
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007b7">Figure 117</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007b7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007b7" filename="../figg13/G13007b7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 117. Remove Rear Bearing Cover, Rear Bearing and Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the gasket mounting surface of gasket material (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007b7">Figure 117</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the rear bearing cover oil seal; replace if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007b8">Figure 118</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007b8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007b8" filename="../figg13/G13007b8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 118. Inspect Rear Bearing Cover Oil Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing inner spacer from the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007b9">Figure 119</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007b9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007b9" filename="../figg13/G13007b9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 119. Remove Bearing Inner Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the output shaft assembly gear front face as a base and press the output shaft through
                the bearing and gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007c0">Figure 120</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007c0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007c0" filename="../figg13/G13007c0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 120. Press Output Shaft Through Bearing and Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
